-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ybh1665702934742.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ybh1665702934742.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ybh1665702934742.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ybh1665702934742\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Naming Rules for DB2\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ybh1665702934742__p_d49331e1_d49332e1_d49333e1\">Observe the following general rules for names:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ybh1665702934742__li_d24026e1_d24027e1_d24028e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ybh1665702934742__p_d49334e1_d49335e1_d49336e1\">Letters, numbers, and underscores (_) are allowed, but the first character must be a letter.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ybh1665702934742__li_d24029e1_d24030e1_d24031e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ybh1665702934742__p_d49337e1_d49338e1_d49339e1\">Uniface accepts only uppercase names in the application model definition.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ybh1665702934742__li_d24032e1_d24033e1_d24034e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ybh1665702934742__p_d49340e1_d49341e1_d49342e1\">Try not to use DB2 reserved words for the names of entities or fields. These reserved words are listed in the DB2 documentation.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ybh1665702934742__p_d49343e1_d49344e1_d49345e1\">However, you can instruct the connector to accept certain DB2 reserved words as field or table names by using the <code class=\"ph codeph\">identifiers:quoted</code> option.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ybh1665702934742__li_d24035e1_d24036e1_d24037e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ybh1665702934742__p_d49346e1_d49347e1_d49348e1\">Table names must also comply with Uniface rules.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ybh1665702934742__section_tlv_gbk_3cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d744643e90\">Index Names</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ybh1665702934742__p_d49352e1_d49353e1_d49354e1\">Index names have a maximum length of 30\n            characters.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ybh1665702934742__section_xnd_3bk_3cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d744643e99\">Table Names</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ybh1665702934742__p_d49358e1_d49359e1_d49360e1\">Table names have a maximum length of 30 characters.\n            Names that are longer will cause errors to be returned.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ybh1665702934742__p_d49361e1_d49362e1_d49363e1\">On iSeries,\n            table names longer than 10 characters will result in physical file names that are\n            truncated to 5 characters and a 5 digit number appended. This is transparent to Uniface\n            and to SQL, but it is not transparent to native iSeries RPG, COBOL, or CL programs or\n            commands, so it is better to choose a name that is no longer than 10 characters.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ybh1665702934742__section_kgs_jbk_3cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d744643e111\">Field Names</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ybh1665702934742__p_d49367e1_d49368e1_d49369e1\">Field names have a maximum length of 30 characters.\n            Names that are longer will cause errors to be returned.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ybh1665702934742__p_d49370e1_d49371e1_d49372e1\">On iSeries,\n            when a field name is longer than 10 characters, it is truncated to 5 characters and a 5\n            digit number appended. For Uniface and SQL, this is transparent, but possibly not to\n            external RPG, COBOL, or CL programs or commands. However, the original long name is\n            preserved in the Column Heading and in the Alternative name of the field.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7832786\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7832786\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Naming Rules for DB2 Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Naming Rules for DB2 Observe the following general rules for names: Letters, numbers, and underscores (_) are allowed, but the first character must be a letter. Uniface accepts only uppercase names in the application model definition. Try not to use DB2 reserved words for the names of entities or fields. These reserved words are listed in the DB2 documentation. However, you can instruct the connector to accept certain DB2 reserved words as field or table names by using the identifiers:quoted option. Table names must also comply with Uniface rules. Index Names Index names have a maximum length of 30 characters. Table Names Table names have a maximum length of 30 characters. Names that are longer will cause errors to be returned. On iSeries, table names longer than 10 characters will result in physical file names that are truncated to 5 characters and a 5 digit number appended. This is transparent to Uniface and to SQL, but it is not transparent to native iSeries RPG, COBOL, or CL programs or commands, so it is better to choose a name that is no longer than 10 characters. Field Names Field names have a maximum length of 30 characters. Names that are longer will cause errors to be returned. On iSeries, when a field name is longer than 10 characters, it is truncated to 5 characters and a 5 digit number appended. For Uniface and SQL, this is transparent, but possibly not to external RPG, COBOL, or CL programs or commands. However, the original long name is preserved in the Column Heading and in the Alternative name of the field. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}